{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The embedding vector produced for a given query string has the correct dimensionality for the vector database index.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"LLM-DEP/AI-DEP applies because the behavior is about the real model output contract (vector length), not just wrapper wiring. PROOF-BUNDLE: phrase forcing level is \"embedding vector produced for a given query string\". Adjacent lower-level miss (Integration): a stubbed embedding client can be hardcoded to expected dimension and always pass, while the real provider/model version returns a different dimension and causes index-write/query failures; this is specifically missed because the failure is in real model output, not generic module wiring. Rejection-gate: System was considered for real network/API, but disqualified because the critical failure boundary here is model-output dependency rather than OS/network behavior itself.","test_description":"Call the actual configured embedding model with a fixed query string in test environment, then assert returned vector length exactly equals the active vector-index dimension (and fail on any mismatch).","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.12,"Integration":0.28,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.52,"Workflow":0.03}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"The similarity search returns results ordered by descending cosine similarity score.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS indicates a module-boundary risk (search service + vector DB adapter/index behavior). Integration-brake checks: (a) no required OS/network/subprocess boundary in the behavior itself; can run against local/in-process vector DB fixture. (b) correctness does not depend on AI/ML judgment quality. (c) no multi-agentic chain. Rejection-gate: Unit was rejected because pure local sort-function tests miss DB retrieval/order handoff behavior.","test_description":"Seed a local test index with known vectors, qu