erministic score thresholds, not model judgment quality. (c) no multi-agentic sequence required. Rejection-gate: Agentic considered but disqualified because behavior text does not require judging semantic quality from real model output; it requires enforcing empty-on-low-similarity policy.","test_description":"Populate local index with vectors intentionally far from the query embedding (or inject low-score retrieval outputs through real retrieval module), execute search, and assert API returns an empty list and does not emit below-threshold items.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.18,"Integration":0.64,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.06,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"The end-to-end latency from receiving the query to returning re-ranked results stays below 2 seconds for the median case.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"REAL-INFRA dominates: this is an end-to-end latency SLO across real HTTP request handling and external model/vector calls. In-process fakes hide real network/serialization/provider latency, so MOCK-HIDE applies. Rejection-gate: Agentic considered but disqualified because assertion is timing, not model-output correctness; real model nondeterministic judgment is not what pass/fail depends on.","test_description":"Run a reproducible load test against the deployed API path (real HTTP) with production-like dependencies enabled, collect end-to-end latencies over a representative sample, and assert median (p50) < 2.0s.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.79,"Agentic":0.1,"Workflow":0.03}}]}
